Package net.sourceforge.gjtapi.util

Interface Summary
EventHandler This is an interface that describes the event processing actions of an event.
 

Class Summary
BaseManager This is a queue that accepts objects and processes these objects.
BlockManager This is a queue that accepts objects and processes these objects.
Cache This is an abstract cache Map of keys to values where the values are held in References which will allow them to be collected by a garbage collector when memory gets low.
EventManager This is a queue that accepts objects manages a collection of event handlers.
ExceptionHandler This is a class that encapsulates how to handle thread running exceptions.
NullExceptionHandler This is a class that encapsulates how to handle thread running exceptions.
OrderedBlockManager This is like an OrderedEventManger except that the events are assumed to be instances of EventHandler themselves.
OrderedEventManager This is an ordered event manager in which one thread serially takes each event off of a queue and asks an EventHandler to process the event.
SoftMap This is a Map of keys to values where the values are held in SoftReferences which will allow them to be collected by a garbage collector when memory gets low.
WeakMap This is a Map of keys to values where the values are held in WeakReferences which will allow them to be collected by a garbage collector at the next opportunity.
